I like your contribution but I am curious why you re-encoded the audio with DOLBY DIGITAL SURROUND 5.2, but your source is stereo 2 channel sound. Its not going create out of nothing 8 channel surround if the source has only 2 channels. AAC is great for CD's and HI Fi Stereo, but doesn't support multi channel audio sources even if there was one included.... AC3 is what can use a multi channel surround source and keeps its integrity. I have yet to find a copy that is in surround sound of ANY kind. ANY type of surround sound be it DTS, THX, DOLBY DIGITAL 1 or 2, is far better then the best stereo (at least for a movie). If someone was able to rip a DVD or even a screener, it would have had the surround signal embedded in the file. I'll wait for an AC3 copy to come out... I did download this and the video is awesome, the audio... not so much? . Thanks for the effort. ANYONE whos willing to try to contribute is appreciated!
